@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

        First of all, let me wish you a merry, merry @{fg shine}C@{fg fill}h@{b}@{fg text}r@{i}@{ub}@{fg shine}i@{ui}@{fg text}s@{fg fill}t@{fg text}m@{fg shine}a@{fg fill}s@{fg text} (yep, it's
today!) and a happy New Year! :)

        @{fg shine}RDBArc@{fg text} in a simpliest way lets you write a @{"Rigid Disk Block" link "RDB" 0} of your
Hard Drive to any file on diskette. This file can be rewritten to Hard Drive
after a eg. attack of some virus (they very often attack @{"RDB" link "RDB" 0}, because it's
most important place on HD). It's very important to do such archives of @{"RDB" link "RDB" 0},
because damage of it is very dangerous and almost always damages all the
data on HD. Then you need to reinstall and reformat HD by HDToolBox!
@{b}Beware!@{ub}

        @{fg shine}RDBArc@{fg text} has a very nice GUI and also can display some information
about loaded RDB. It prevents you eg. by the loading of some wrong file. I
think @{fg shine}RDBArc@{fg text} is very useful for some Amigants that are not even average.
It's simple to use and makes all work automaticly. 

        Plaese read this @{"WARNING" link "WARNING" 0}
@endnode

@node "Instructions" "Instructions"

        Program runs both from CLI or Workbench. From CLI you can use
following arguments:

@{fg fill}AUTOREADRDB=AR/S@{fg text}

If you'll set this switch on @{fg shine}RDBArc@{fg text}, after loading, will automaticly read
the @{"RDB" link "RDB" 0} on your Hard Drive. It's not really useful, because the @{"Read RDB" link "Instructions" 40}
gadget makes the same work.

@{fg fill}SCSI/K/N@{fg text}

It's very important argument if you have more than one SCSI drive. Using
this you tell the program, from witch SCSI unit it will read/write @{"RDB" link "RDB" 0}.
Default it's set to ZERO.

@{fg fill}CHECKRDBPOS=CRDB/S@{fg text}

This switch should not be normally used, but in some situations it may be
very important to set it. On most HDs the RDB block starts from hardware
block 0. But if you have RDB on other block (up to 16) you MUST set this
switch on. With this, program will automaticly search for position of RDB on
HD, and then save RDB.

        When running from Workbench, you can set these tooltypes:

        @{fg fill}AUTOREADRDB=YES|NO
        CHECKRDBPOSITION=YES|NO
        SCSI=<numer urz‚dzenia>@{fg text}

        They work identical to CLI arguments.


        After running, program will display window with some buttons and one
big listview gadget. This biggest gadget contains some useful information
about currently loaded in buffer RDB. This information you can scroll
up/down with two cursors.

        Gadgets are:

@{fg highlight}Read RDB@{fg text}

Loads the @{"RDB" link "RDB" 0} from HD to the buffer. Listview automaticly lists all the
information from RDB.

@{fg highlight}Write RDB@{fg text}

Writes RDB in buffer to your HD. Please, be careful, and first read this
very important @{"WARNING" link "WARNING" 0}!

@{fg highlight}Load File@{fg text}

Now you can load any RDB file to buffer. Note, that if file doesn't exist,
the buffer will be cleared. If file doesn't contain any RDB, requester will
be shown, and buffer will be cleared eighter.

@{fg shine}Write File@{fg text}

Here you can write buffer to any file. Just choose a filename by the ASL
requester.

@{fg shine}About@{fg text}

Surprise!
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "System requirements"

        Program needs ASL.library to work and any SCSI device with your
Amiga (eg. AT-BUS Hard Drive). It should work on Kickstart 2.0+ but was
tested only on Kickstart 3.0! No memory expansion required.

        @{fg shine}RDBArc@{fg text} was written in Amiga E 3.1i. Source code is about 22kb long
and binary has about 16Kb. It was tested on this machine:

        Amiga 1200, KS3.0, HDD Conner 1030MB 1.30, M-Tec 030/38 turbo, 8MB
Fast RAM.

        Also Enoforcer was used for tests.
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"

        In this (very fast - made in 3 days) version some bugs may appear,
wich I would like to remove. You can be sure that program writes/reads RDB
without problems (If it doesn't, why my HD is still OK? ;) In comparison
with ReadRDB by Gerard Cornu, @{fg shine}RDBArc@{fg text} has a lot of good sides and... looks
better :)

        I'd like to localize this program in 100%. Now listview isn't
localized.
@endnode

